G.2 Deployment of Own POS Terminals as POS Acquiring Bank
37. A UCB intending to act as POS acquiring bank shall be permitted to deploy its own POS terminals with prior approval of RBI subject to fulfilling the following criteria:
(1) A UCB shall comply with the criteria that: (i) the UCB is licensed by RBI and is Core Banking Solution (CBS) compliant; (ii) the CRAR is not less than nine percent in the preceding financial year; (iii) the UCB has recorded a net profit in the preceding financial year; (iv) the Board of the UCB consists of at least two professional directors; (v) the UCB has a Board approved customer grievance redressal mechanism; (vi) the UCB has put in place a policy approved by the Board for merchant acquisition for card transactions; and (vii) there are no restrictions imposed on the UCB for accepting deposits / withdrawals by the RBI;
(2) The IT systems and CBS of the UCB shall have been subjected to an IS Audit not earlier than six months from the date of application, certifying that the systems are adequately secure;
(3) The assessed net-worth of the UCB shall be more than ₹25 crore as per the last RBI inspection;
(4) The Gross NPA of the UCB shall be less than seven percent and net NPAs shall be less than three percent in the preceding financial year;
(5) A UCB shall not have been subjected to any monetary penalty by the RBI during the last two financial years and during the year of submitting application;
(6) There shall not be any default in the maintenance of CRR / SLR during the preceding financial year; and
(7) A UCB shall be a member of authorized card network, such as RuPay, Visa, or MasterCard, etc.

A UCB shall be eligible to apply for a license as Authorized Dealers (AD) Category I / II subject to compliance with the following norms:
(1) AD Category-l
(i) A UCB shall be included in the Second Schedule to RBI Act 1934;
(ii) A UCB shall have a minimum net worth of ₹200 crore;
(iii) The CRAR shall not be less than 12 percent;
(iv) The gross NPA shall not exceed 10 percent;
(v) A UCB shall have made profit in the preceding three years;
(vi) A UCB shall have no defaults in maintenance of CRR / SLR requirements;
(vii) A UCB shall have sound internal control systems; and
(viii) A UCB shall have an elected board of management with at least two professionals.
(2) AD Category II
(i) A UCB shall have a minimum net worth of ₹10 crore;
(ii) The CRAR shall not be less than nine percent;
(iii) The gross NPAs shall not exceed 10 percent;
(iv) A UCB shall have made profit in the preceding three years;
(v) A UCB shall have no defaults in maintenance of CRR / SLR requirements;
(vi) A UCB shall have sound internal control systems; and
(vii) A UCB shall have an elected board of management with at least two professional directors.

