B.2 Categorization of UCBs:
3. The UCBs have been categorized into following four tiers for regulatory purposes:
(1) Tier 1 - All unit UCBs and salary earners' UCBs (irrespective of deposit size), and all other UCBs having deposits up to ₹100 crore;
(2) Tier 2 - UCBs with deposits more than ₹100 crore and up to ₹1000 crore;
(3) Tier 3 - UCBs with deposits more than ₹1000 crore and up to ₹10,000 crore;
(4) Tier 4 - UCBs with deposits more than ₹10,000 crore.

